  "prompt": "Was Khizr Khan paid over 100k by CNN and NBC and 175k by the DNC?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no publicly available evidence or credible reports indicating that Khizr Khan was paid over $100,000 by CNN and NBC or $175,000 by the Democratic National Committee (DNC). Khizr Khan became widely known for his impactful speech at the 2016 Democratic National Convention, where he addressed issues related to his family's military service and criticized then-presidential candidate Donald Trump.\n\nWhile Khizr Khan has been involved in various speaking engagements and advocacy efforts since then, specific financial transactions or substantial payments from major media organizations like CNN and NBC, or the DNC, have not been substantiated in reliable sources. It's important to approach such claims with caution and verify them through reputable news outlets or official statements.\n\nIf there have been developments or disclosures after October 2023, I would recommend consulting trusted news sources or official financial disclosures for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
